title: For Sale:  sks with a Lot of upgrades
location: Santa Fe, NM, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
When I bought this rifle last summer, it already had this ATI tactical folding stock on it. My opinion is that this is a far superior stock to the cheap Tapcos out there.  This stock was not fitted correctly when I got it, so I went to work and fitted it right. The ATI doesn't allow for the folding bayonet to be attached for a reason (sorry zombie hunters, lol). It is solid in the forearm area, and has a Picatinney rail there to allow attachment of accessories including lights and a vertical for grip. This is a much better system and allows better accuracy as well. There are also accessory rails on the sides of the forearm. the have covers also.

Since have fitted the removable covers to the rails,  it is quite comfortable to grip securely. If you want a vertical grip, good. Because that will come with it too. I regularly shoot this rifle at 220 meters offhand with superb accuracy, and have it set up to be a 10 of 10 on a gallon milk jug at that range. Basically anything inside 300 meters is a lock. I know that sounds like a stretch, but it isn't. 

Here are some other upgrades: Matching blued bolt (looks like Russian), high visibility front sight, upgraded gas piston, AK74 type muzzle break,  folding four position buttstock, bolt modification to allow mag changes with the bolt closed, trigger job, Mil-spec butt pad, four custom fitted 30 round Tapco polymer magazines, one US steel magazine, upgraded firing pin, polished and tuned action. One custom fitted 5-round hunting magazine (pigs are always in season in New Mexico) I am forgetting some.

It will also come with its original ten round fixed magazine as well, but you will probably never install it. This is a chrome lined bore, so minimal cleaning, and it just has superb accuracy and reliability. I have NEVER had a failure to eject, feed, or fire with it.

If you like to shoot but don't want to pay high prices for ammunition, the 7.62x39 is a great round. Prices range from $5.19 a box at Walmart (and they always have it) to about $6.00 a box at local sporting goods stores. So this is cheap shooting and ammunition is always available. I have had zero problems getting it. Power is on par with a .30-30, but recoil on these gas operated rifles is almost nil. My 5'2, 110 pound wife can shoot it all day.

Ok, so if this one is so great, why am I selling it, and why so cheap? Simple. Two reasons: I like to build these rifles and when they are tuned and finished, I want to build another one. The second reason is that while I shoot these I don't collect them I collect old Russian bolt actions and I need room for more of those. 

So if you have read this far and want a rifle that can protect your home or want one to hunt with - or just want one to play with, I think this one would be a pretty good choice. Even you Zombie hunters might like it. There are more than $100 worth of magazines alone that will go with this rifle, and another couple of hundred in upgrades, plus labor to do it. If you have wanted an SKS but they don't fit you because the stock is too short, don't worry. This one will extend out past where even I need to go, and I am 6'2'. It's quite comfortable.

Contact me through Armslist with your phone number an we can arrange to meet in person. You will like this SKS. Frankly if I hadn't bought 15 rifles in the past 5 weeks, I would not be selling it.

Thanks for reading.
Doby Pilgrim
Santa Fe
